-- Iran’s Rial Drops as U.S. Institutes New Sanctions, Mehr Reports
-- B y   C l a u d i a   M a e d l e r
-- 2012-01-02T16:20:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-02/iran-s-rial-drops-as-u-s-institutes-new-sanctions-mehr-reports.html
Iran ’s rial weakened against the
dollar, two days after the U.S. instituted new sanctions
targeting Iran’s  central bank  over Tehran’s nuclear drive, the
state-run  Mehr news agency  reported.  The rial was being exchanged at 17,800 to the dollar in
street markets late today, compared with the Dec. 29 rate of
15,200 rials to the dollar, Mehr said.  The official rate for today was 11,180 rials a dollar,
according to the Central Bank’s website. The average rate
offered at currency exchange bureaus was about 15,300 rials a
dollar in late December.  To contact the reporter on this story:
